  "prompt": "What is a Walmart Rollback? What are they for?",
  "response": "A Walmart Rollback is a temporary price reduction on a specific product that is meant to offer customers savings. Unlike clearance items, which are typically discontinued products, Rollback items are actively stocked products that Walmart has decided to sell at a lower price for a limited time. The goal of a Rollback is to:\n\n1. Attract customers with lower prices\n2. Increase sales volume\n3. Provide value to shoppers\n4. Compete with other retailers' pricing\n5. Clear excess inventory\n\nRollbacks can occur on various types of products, including groceries, electronics, home goods, clothing, and more. The price reduction is usually prominent in-store and online, with special signage or labels highlighting the savings.",
